[http://dachary.org/ Loic Dachary] has been involved with the Free Software Movement since 1987, when he started distributing GNU tapes to the general public in France. In 2012 he founded [http://upstream-university.org/ Upstream University], a nonprofit with the goal of teaching developers how to contribute easily and efficiently. Dachary volunteers as a developer for [http://april.org/ April], a grassroots organization promoting Free Software. He maintains April's [http://openstack.org/ OpenStack] cluster and organizes contributions with agile methods. As President of FSF France, he also provides technical and legal resources to French Free Software developers. His day job is to use and contribute to [http://ceph.com/ ceph] within [http://openstack.org/ OpenStack].








